video_title: NEW Season 3 FragPunk Lancer - Counterfeit | One Becomes Many
author: @Blade23445
comment_text: Seeing some of the comments to this video I’m happy she can’t swap between her mirages or anything wild like that. Counterfeit is probably one of the most insane characters currently in the game, as a Nitro main her scans basically directly counter any wall positions you might have (especially the offensive one.) in duels she can fake push different angles and sneak to the other site to get a free pick (up to 3 times.) you actually can cancel her 2 pretty much as soon as you activate it utilizing her 3 and can throw enemies off guard with it. Sure her skill floor is about as high as Dex. But her skill ceiling is on par if not higher than spider. Can’t wait to see what tech gets discovered for her kit pretty soon as the season progresses.

From a business perspective, the Premium BP is semi free/for F2P players and their quality is therefore on par or better than all the other free/F2P skins.
Just my 2 cents.

Snipers aren't the worst. They can be nerfed yes but they should 1 shot. I have explained how in previous comments. You can also nerf snipers by buffing the util pistols. Make flashing enemies more forgiving. Sometimes if the flash is but barely above the enemy pov it flashes them barely. 

All tactical fps use utility and thats what defines average from good players. They might be underpowered but something is for sure ppl are not using them enough.

Reality of it is because of how easy it is to climb no one will take it so seriously. And i just went on a random rant for nor reason.

I wont delete it because it took me a while to write out my thoughts lol

video_title: ITS TOO HARD | FragPunk Introduces PvE Tower Defense Mode
author: @SaadAsfaq
comment_text:
I honestly enjoy how it is rn, I like having to brain storm to find out what works and then going up in difficulty makes me switch it all up again, I managed to beat the first handful of levels on nightmare so far, and I will say I do think its a lil overdone I just feel like I'm constantly begging for more crystals and I do wish the turrets were a tad more powerful because it does feel like you need a fair amount of investment to get them to work.

I found nitro using smart chug chug or summons to draw agro and keep enemies in a kill gate of turrets is the best way to get value out of them so far, you can also take advantage of all the enemies piling up to deal decent AOE damage with explosions or a greatsword

video_title: Why Don't You Like FragPunk?
author: @sorenkair
comment_text:
rank inflation is the worst ive seen in any game. ppl can hit master with negative winrate. im very average at tacshooters, peaked gold in csgo and valo, but i hit diamond in 60 hours, master in like 90, i was master 2 when season 2 ended and i probably could have made it to punkmaster as i was still maintaing a good winrate but i was only playing 1 or 2 games a day at that point. it really makes ranks feel worthless and a waste of time to grind for.

the eomm is also atrocious just like marvel rivals, more than half of my games are one sided stomps and no fun at all.

the balancing in the event modes is also horrendous (toxic smoke chum) but i wont complain too much because its just for fun.

video_title: Why Don't You Like FragPunk?
author: @trickynickofficial
comment_text:
I’ve been thinking about this a lot, too - especially how you go from 100K to 3K concurrent on Steam almost overnight, and more importantly, how do we get back to where we were? Here’s everything I/we came up with followed by my responses any time I hear or read similar comments:

Complaint 1: Uses AI. 
Answer: I have NEVER EVER seen any comment, thread, video, etc. anywhere that has proven this. As you stated, Steam takes this very seriously, so the financial risk to Bad Guitar, and more importantly NetEase (Marvel Rivals), is therefore substantial.

Complaint 2: Movement speed nerfed and sliding removed from Beta to Launch. 
Answer: They made an intentional design decision for balanced, fair gameplay and to be more of a tactical shooter leaning towards realism. Unless I’m mistaken, there is no combat training anywhere in the world where you’re taught that your most optimal response when engaging enemies in a firefight is to jump up and down and slide at them.

Complaint 3: Too many female characters and “girly” skins. 
Answer: I have NEVER seen an FPS with this many female and non-binary players and not only am I proud to be a member of this community (and to say we have 2 female Club members and growing), but the game’s community is also much better for it. It’s downright refreshing, and I commend Bad Guitar for their continued tasteful, inclusive (on several fronts) efforts.

The truth, however, about all my answers is that none of them are going to change, so I don’t unfortunately have an answer to my question of “How do we get back to where we were?”. We can only hope that Bad Guitar does, and all I can say is of actual players that I talk to now, nearly everyone only ever has great things to say about the game.

Don't forget the game also took a bit of a hit in the beginning cause console got delayed. People forgot about it.

I mean I feel like that for the past couple of years most shooters that have been released are just being hated no matter what. Most of the complains oftentimes just seem very contradictory. I constantly hear people screaming that they want to have something new and unique but when they get something new and unique they complain that it's boring, too confusing, "too different" or sometimes, somehow they'll say it's actually not original or interesting even if the mechanics introduced are completely new/very rare in a genre. You just can't satisfy current shooter players. 
BUT at the end of the day if someone doesn't like the game it's their own business. Even tho I love for example Fragpunk I don't say that if you don't like it you're dumb. I'm just saying that I feel that many people scream they want something they themselves even don't know what it is.

author: @STR8BASEMENTPROD
comment_text:
I just recently quit for the following reasons.

1. peakers advantage is absolutely not acceptable and unfun in EVERY way possible. someone being able to see u on the reverse angle but you can’t see them is just plain STUPID. this is exactly why valorant spent efforts to fix this and is more popular. plain and simple it's unfun and unfair.

2. ping, cheaters, mouse and key vs controller on console. just plain stupid. there not the same input for a reason and it shouldn't be allowed.Many games don’t allow this for obvious reasons, overwatch as an example, it doesnt allow this and if you try to use mouse and keyboard on console it puts you with pc players to keep it balanced. 

3. they don't advertise the game for shit...
guns are not  balanced, and with peakers advantage, sniping is just plain ridicules unfun a typical patter here…seeing someone for a split second and dying in one hit is not fun.

comment_text:
•Fever and snipers are still extremely annoying to play against with no nerfs to either in sight 🤮 
•No new shard clash maps with a constant emphasis on these limited time modes 
•skins and shard cards being the only thing added/updated that have any real effort put into them 
•nerfing lancers in the dumbest ways possible and not really even buffing the weaker ones to bring them up at all
I still enjoy the game to an extent but it’s gotten so stale in ranked/standard that I find myself playing arcade modes if I want to actually have fun

video_title: Why Don't You Like FragPunk?
author: @Tacticalpotato.
comment_text:
I recently deleted it:
Personal issues: I have poor ping.

Things that moved me away: Bots, long matchmaking, did in a way feel like a mobile game when I tried navigating the events (Which is fine, but i didn't love it), and snipers... I just don't like that I can use ARs the same amount as a oneshot sniper.

I did like: The character designs, art style, cards, easy to unlock the people you want, and the amount of free events (Just the mobile game feel is a necessary evil to have all the events)

I enjoyed it when ping wasn't a problem, but it seems to be really demanding in that regard, and i feel other games just handle poor ping better. But that's a me problem, 7/10 game, i just feel there are better options in the genre.

author: @PixelKnight46
comment_text: It's being hypocritical for the sake of it. So much of the points these people make barely try the game. Lancers are "expensive" because it's giving the game content, something to grind for, and you could max the battle pass to get the bonus points to exchange for a bunch of gold for it (more ways to grind). And I don't think they have the capacity to navigate the somewhat simple and intuitive menu's (imo) to find all the free wars. People complain about bots and leave, well, they're actively contributing to the problem, just keep playing and the player count will go up gradually. To be honest, the only good thing to come from these reviews is that these people are outing themselves in the community because I wouldn't want them to stick around.

video_title: AMAZING News For FragPunk! Are We Back?
author: @knexfan100
comment_text:
I'm very sick of games trying to shoehorn e-sports. e-sports is best when it's a grassroots movement that grows from the player base itself like how counterstrike works. Counterstrike will never die because it was a grassroots e-sports movement since the early 2000s..... and a lot of these events were pay per view to keep the e-sports model actually sustainable instead of just draining venture capital funds to fill a stupid stadium... The only way to encourage that kind of growth is to give us a way to have private servers and lan parties.... 

This feeds into building small communities that want to play against each other: Give us a better clan (called clubs in the game) system. 10 members per clan is stupid..... I can't even fit my whole squad in 10 members... A lot of us have more than 10 friends. 

Once they figure out a good clan system and a way to facilitate competition between those clans both officially and unofficially, e-sports will just naturally happen after a few years... Best part is NetEase doesn't even have to fund the events if they go this route.... It's literally free hype, which is exactly how CSGO blew up in 2014.... The only thing in that major that valve paid for was the prize pool. Everything else was paid for by the event organizers.... It was enough free hype that me and seven of my friends immediately started saving money to build better/new gaming PCs to play Counter-Strike.... 

Going back to the private servers thing, I would love to play this game on faceit servers where I'm guaranteed to have the best netcode on the market.... This game still has 30 tick rate servers, which is not even close to enough for a game that's trying to be anyway competitive or fair between gunfights....

video_title: AMAZING News For FragPunk! Are We Back?
author: @sencha_VA
comment_text: Fragpunk really needs to decide if they're going to be the "fun/casual" shooter or tighten up for an E-sports run. I sincerely hope it's the former rather than the latter. I personally enjoy watching tournaments, but it is doing NOTHING to expand the playerbase or even keep what it has. Push the fun. Market the humorous more laid back aspects and maintain the soul of the game. I don't want to support bickering or fighting amongst the tac-shooter space, but they need to make the difference between Siege/Valo/CS and Fragpunk a focal point of their marketing. People want a stress free shooter, BE THAT! I know a lot of people sick of Valo and Siege because of how sweaty and toxic they are, but in the early days of Siege it was a fun game to kick back joke around in. I remember setting up Tachanka's turret and getting zero kills while everyone laughed at the absurdity. I remember stacking Lesion mines in doorways for a funny kill and tricking my friends into jumping on Frost mats. Now every player is miserable chasing some pro-league strat they saw in some video and complaining. I am begging the dev team to take further chances and stand out from all of that.

comment_text: I'm going to keep it so real with you unc, I'm happy we can agree that the tournaments don't matter as much as people believe they do. I have hundreds of hours played and have participated in some community tournaments myself; however, the attention these tournaments get is lackluster at most. Retrospectively, twitter has received massive numbers for the Shard Verse tour, pathogen clown skin, ect. It doesn't take a genius to compare the numbers.  Returning skins to focus on marketing is arguably the best thing they couldn've done, if not the only thing, to salvage player count. The year roadmap they laid out primarily focused on events and skins, leading the focus of the dev team to ensure everything was perfect. Rereleasing the older skins will give just enough of a break across all the teams to move focus elsewhere. anyways ur smelly unc

video_title: AMAZING News For FragPunk! Are We Back?
author: @waffals1
comment_text:
​​@citrunyThat is actually how a lot of things are. If you want milk that's good for 3 weeks, you will pay full price. When the milk is about to go bad, they sell it for less.
If you go to a concert and purchase a shirt, you will pay full price. When the tour is over you will pay slightly less and not need to purchase a ticket to the show.
Even Fortnite does this with the bundle skins (Purple joker/Midas/ivy, Skeleton Crew, etc) the packs aren't always available and they come back at a discount. The company still makes money and the consumer gets a deal on old skins that are only available in the bundle.
Plus sales economics incentivizes more people to purchase stuff, so it would boost the funding for the game.

comment_text:
Gostei que as armas são cheias de detalhes, tanto na sua contrução, material e animações que fazem referência a F1.

Um exemplo são o número de cilindros que aparece a cima do cano, você tem V8, V12 e um 4I. 

As armas também possuem detalhes de estofamentos (como na empunhadura do pega mão) e detalhes em carbono na coronha, outro detalhe do peta mão é a costura em linha branca que lembra a costura se um banco ou forro.

Até as rodas apresentam alguns detalhes, de início imaginei que pudessem usar a variação de pneus de acordo com a realidade, aonde se tem compostos diferentes para situações de pista diferentes. Mas aqui optaram por trazer o conjunto da roda como um todo que lembra até outras categorias e não apenas a F1 (A última roda por exemplo, você acaba vendo bastante nas categorias de GT - Gran Turismo) 

Vamos Fragpunk 
Vamos, pegue todo o meu dinheiro, canalha!

comment_text:
Fala Paulo! Beleza? 

Não tem muito a ver com o assunto do vídeo, mas beleza kkk Eu tenho uma ideia que pode ser boa para talvez chamar um cenário competitivo pro jogo.

Seguinte: Ao invés de cartas aleatórias, criar um mercado de cartas durante as partidas parecido com o que acontece no modo novo, mas sem essa coisa de baralho, mas com cartas fixadas para CT e TR, sem as cartas que decidem e economia separada das armas como é. Exemplo: 

- Loja CT:  Tem as cartas que funcionam só para defesa, como as que facilitam o defuse e outras cartas como aquela smoke venenosa, etc
- Loja TR: Tem cartas que funcionam só para ataque, como a plantação arremesso e TAMBÉM contaria com a smoke venenosa, etc

Ou seja, um mercado fixado que muda só as cartas que só funcionam para um lado com economia decidida entre o time, sem as cartas que definem round sozinha e mais cartas táticas.

Se achar interessante, tenta passar para os devs 😅 acho que pode funcionar
